A MAN believed to be a vagrant living next to the railway has died.He was crushed by a train at the railway line below Joe Slovo and Dennis Webster Streets in the Durban CBD yesterday.A witness told Daily Sun he was one of the homeless people living next to the railway. &ldquo;They&rsquo;ve built plastic shacks and take drugs. He was knocked over by a train while trying to cross to the other side.&rdquo; Rescue Care Paramedics spokesman Garrith Jamieson said: &ldquo;The man believed to be in his 30s was run over by a train. The cops&rsquo; search and rescue unit and Metro police were at the scene. We&rsquo;re trying to find what led to it.&rdquo; Captain Nqobile Gwala confirmed the incident. &ldquo;At 9am a 30-year-old man crossing the railway line was allegedly knocked over and died. An inquest will be opened for investigation,&rdquo; she said.